On Monday, September 04, 2006, at 01:17PM, paulnather(-at-)bis.midco.net <paulnather(-at-)bis.midco.net> wrote:

>Anyhow, I have removed the pushrods (dripping in oil)but how in the world
>do you get the pushrod tubes out?  There's nothing to grab hold of!

You need to grab them from below with wide mouth pliers (very gently) and wiggle them out. You only need to move them 10 cm or so before the seals break free.

